name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 11/ Apple was singled out in $ADI 10-K filings as being responsible for more than 10% of revenue for the fiscal years 2015 to 2017. name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 7/ The Jul 2020 $ADI presentation mentioned earlier says the combination of $ADI & 120-bagger $MXIM will have an EV of $68 Bn w/ 31% or $21 Bn belonging to $MXIM. $ADI CEO Roche notes that they are known for wireless comm. & that $MXIM will help w/ wireline.  https://t.co/2OoeaxAtTY

name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 5/ Capital Returns by Palgrave Macmillan & Edward Chancellor was written in 2015 before the $LLTC acquisition & it praises both $ADI & $LLTC as separate companies. It notes that employees can be sticky on the analog side of the semiconductor industry relative to the digital side.

name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 4/ The $ADI 2017  https://t.co/iwEDgIOim9 investor day presentation shows that $ADI was already strong with Converters & Amplifiers while $LLTC ignited their Power Management revenue. It also talks about revenue going from $250 to $600 per car.  https://t.co/ZsHFJDvI8A

name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 3/ Seeing as $LLTC was acquired in the middle of the FY17, the $ADI 10-K through Oct 2018 is telling; Industrial rose from 44% of revenue in FY16 to 50% in FY18. Consumer fell from 20% to 14% while Automotive & Communications remained at 16% & 20%, respectively.

name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 1/ Investing $10,000 in Analog Devices $ADI back in Oct 1973 brought about over $12 Mn by 2014 per the 100 Baggers book.
